{
  "texts": [
    "Each transformer block in Restormer utilizes a novel multi-Dconv head transposed attention system, enabling the capture of both local and non-local interactions through query-key feature interplay across channels.",
    "Additionally, Restormer incorporates a gated feed-forward network that selectively transmits the most pertinent features, optimizing the flow of information within the network.",
    "Unfolding Transformer (PADUT) addresses key challenges in existing hyperspectral image (HSI) reconstruction methods, such as fixed gradient descent, inadequate 3D handling, and ineffective stage interaction (Li et al. 2023).",
    "PADUT introduces a pixel-adaptive descent step in the data module to specifically target pixel-level degradation.",
    "The prior module incorporates a Non-local Spectral Transformer (NST) to enhance the recovery process by emphasizing the 3D characteristics of HSI."
  ]
}